review_blob: One of few weizenbocks that could be presented to BJCP judges during their course as an example of banana aroma. Tastes like bananas covered in caramel. Drinking two may be a little bit hard (ABV + sweetness above average + a little bit oily texture), but still it is one of the best of that style in my life.
Strong, fruity (mostly citrus) aroma, taste may be a little bit too sweet for some people, but those fruits fix everything. Great job.
Casual, mass-producted porter. Alcohol with a hint of roasted malts. Nothing to be proud of. Looks quite good though.
A very interesting one. I think it could be pine, maybe some juniper berries? Quite flat, no foam (when it got a little warmer, it resembled congac).
beer_name: BrewDog / Flying Dog International Arms Race

review_blob: Piney aroma with hints of citrus fruits and a little bit of alcohol. Well carbonated, copper liquid. Full body, long, bitter finish (very pleasant and worth remembering). Bottle.

Black beer with short living brown foam. Chocolote, roasty, aromas, a little more whiskey notes would be great. Fine taste, quite full body. Not so good as Rowing Jack, but still a great beer from a great brewery.

review_blob:
One of the best or even the best beer that Ive tried in my life. Unfortunately the only IPA in Poland. 
Aroma: hops, resin, citrus & herbs...and hops. Did I mention hops?
Color: amber, red, quite clear
Head: small frothy
Taste: light sweetness, very bitter, lightly sour
Palate: light body, slick feel, average carbonation, bitter, long finish
Coffe aroma is covered by metallic taste and short dry finish.Not my type of porter. Hold a big part of polish "porter market" just because its made by biggest beer company.
